This paper is about deep learning algorithms applied to medical imaging, specifically cardiac MR segmentation. The paper proposes a methodology of latent space factorisation relying on the cycle-consistency principle. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image analysis and segmentation. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of learning good feature representations, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper is about medical imaging, which could also place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
